benchmark_config.jira_title: Implement/Test API: DELETE /1.0/kb/catalog - Delete all versions for a per tenant catalog

covered: Valid Deletion scenarios across multiple test cases (TC01, TC02, TC05, TC10, TC12, TC15) delete all catalog versions successfully
Authorization and header validation (missing header, invalid token, empty header, malicious header, extra headers) (TC03, TC04, TC07, TC11, TC14, TC08)
Data integrity and orphaned references cleanup (TC12)
Empty data post-deletion: GET returns empty or 404 (TC01)
gaps: Soft deletes not covered (hard vs soft delete semantics)
Caching headers behavior (ETag, Cache-Control) for DELETE responses
More explicit validation of error response bodies (e.g., error codes in response)
Edge-case: deletion with malformed URL or trailing slashes (not covered)
recommendations: Add a test for 403 Forbidden when user lacks permission (authenticated but not allowed)
Add soft-delete semantics test if supported or clarify deletion semantics
Introduce rate-limiting tests to ensure throttling and idempotency under load
Add tests for caching semantics on delete responses (ETag/Cache-Control) if applicable
Add explicit validation of error response bodies for header validation cases (400/401/422 responses)
Consider an idempotency-focused test: repeated DELETE on the same tenant should return 204 or 404 appropriately
